===知名作家的一些老旧用法===
早在14世纪的[[中古英语|中古英语]]，they就一直被用于单数形式。{{sfn|Huddleston|Pullum|2002|pp=493–494}}{{sfn|American Heritage Dictionaries|1996|p=178}} 在许多知名作家的著作中都能看来这种用法，包括[[杰弗里·乔叟|杰弗里·乔叟]]、[[威廉·莎士比亚|威廉·莎士比亚]]、[[简·奥斯丁|简·奥斯丁]]、[[威廉·梅克比斯·萨克雷|威廉·梅克比斯·萨克雷]]和[[萧伯纳|萧伯纳]]：
* "And whoso fyndeth hym out of swich blame,
: ''They'' wol come up . . ."
:—Chaucer, ''The Pardoner's Prologue'' (c. 1395);{{sfn|Chaucer|1395|p=195}} 引用自Jespersen在《Merriam-Webster's Concise Dictionary of English Usage》。{{sfn|Merriam-Webster|2002|p=734}}
* " {{'}}Tis meet that some more audience than ''a mother'', since nature makes ''them'' partial, should o'erhear the speech."— Shakespeare, ''[[Hamlet|Hamlet]]'' (1599);{{sfn|Shakespeare|1599|p=105}}引用自《Merriam-Webster's Concise Dictionary of English Usage》。{{sfn|Merriam-Webster|2002|p=735}}
* "If ''a person'' is born of a . . . gloomy temper . . . ''they'' cannot help it."— Chesterfield, 《Letter to his son》 (1759);{{sfn|Chesterfield|1759|p=568}}引用自《Fowler's》。{{sfn|Fowler|1996|p=779}}
* "Now ''nobody'' does anything well that ''they'' cannot help doing"— Ruskin, 《The Crown of Wild Olive》 (1866);{{sfn|Ruskin|1866|p=44}}引用自《Fowler's》。{{sfn|Fowler|1996|p=779}}
* "''Nobody'' in ''their'' senses would give sixpence on the strength of a promissory note of the kind."— Bagehot, 《The Liberal Magazine》 (1910);{{sfn|Bagehot|1910}}引用自《Fowler's》。{{sfn|Fowler|1926|p=648 }}
* "I would have ''every body'' marry if ''they'' can do it properly."— [[Jane_Austen|Austen]],  《Mansfield Park》 (1814);{{sfn|Austen|1814|p=37}}引用自《Merriam-Webster's Concise Dictionary of English Usage》。{{sfn|Merriam-Webster|2002 |p=734}}
* Caesar: "No, Cleopatra. ''No man'' goes to battle to be killed."
: Cleopatra: "But ''they'' do get killed"
:—[[George_Bernard_Shaw|Shaw]],  ''[[Caesar_and_Cleopatra_(play)|Caesar and Cleopatra]]'' (1901);{{sfn|Shaw|1901|p=67}}引用自《Merriam-Webster's Concise Dictionary of English Usage》。{{sfn|Merriam-Webster|2002|p=735}}
* "''A person'' can't help ''their'' birth."— W. M. Thackeray, ''Vanity Fair'' (1848);{{sfn|Thackeray|1868|p=66}}引用自《Merriam-Webster's Concise Dictionary of English Usage》。{{sfn|Merriam-Webster|2002|p=734}}

同时，除了使用they，使用代词he作为（据称的）性别中性代词也被认可{{sfn|Fowler|1996|p=358}}，如下所述：
* "Suppose the life and fortune of ''every one of us'' would depend on ''his'' winning or losing a game of chess."— [[Thomas_Henry_Huxley|Thomas Huxley]], ''A Liberal Education'' (1868);{{sfn|Huxley|1868}}引自Baskervill.{{sfn|Baskervill|1895|loc=§409}}
